e curriculum, and participating actively in student projects and activities.  Established in 2000, CEPAC draws its membership from both professional practitioners—many of whom are UIC alumni—and civil engineering faculty members. Its ranks include leaders in the environmental, geotechnical, structures, transportation, and water resources fields and represent private companies and government agencies throughout the Chicago region.       CEPAC Members     Roster of current individual members         members   UIC alumni are denoted with an asterisk.   Behringer, Thomas J.*, PE, SE – Senior Vice President,  Sargent & Lundy Nuclear Power Technologies  Bendok, Mark R.*, PE, SE – Project Manager, Alfred Benesch & Company  Benitez, Luis D., PE, SE – Chief Bridge Engineer, Chicago DOT  Anne Bigane Wilson, PE, CPC, NAC – President/CEO, Bigane Paving Co.  Brindley, Thomas M., PE – President, Brindley Engineering Corp.  Burke, Christopher B., PhD, PE – President/CEO, Christopher B. Burke Engineering, Ltd.  Davidson, Patricia*, PE – Senior Civil Engineer, T.Y. Lin International, Inc.  Evans, Debra P.* – Senior Program Manager, Hospira, Inc.  Fortmann, John, PE – Deputy Director of Highways/Region 1 Engineer, IDOT District 1  Frangos, Charles*, PE – Managing Partner, Orion Engineers, LLC  Huffman, Matthew* – Project Manager, Christopher B. Burke Engineering, Ltd.  Kochan, Chester F.*, PE – Vice President, Clark Dietz, Inc.  Kos, John P., PE – Vice President, Lochner  Kovacs, Paul D., PE – Chief Engineering Officer, Illinois State Toll Highway Authority  Lewis, Jonathan E., SE – Associate Principal and Unit Manager, Wiss, Janney, Elstner Associates, Inc.  Mulac, Gregory A.*, Vice President, Preconstruction Manager – Turner Construction Company  Nelson, Kenneth E.*, PE – Management Consultant  Podczerwinski, Edward W., PE – Director of Monitoring and Research Department, Metropolitan Water Reclamation District of Greater Chicago  Quigley, Anthony J., PE – Region One Engineer, IDOT